Film4.uk.description: (2018) Revenge thriller with Jennifer Garner. A mum turns vigilante on a quest for justice when her husband and daughter are murdered by a drug cartel.

Film4.uk.title: Stand by Me
Film4.uk.description: (1986) Four young friends (Wil Wheaton, River Phoenix, Corey Feldman, Jerry O'Connell) set out on an expedition into deepest Oregon in this coming-of-age tale based on a Stephen King story.

Film4.uk.title: Deadpool 2
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Ryan Reynolds returns as the potty-mouthed, can of whup-ass-opening superhero and now he's got buddies to help him take on baddie Josh Brolin in the all-out action comedy sequel.

Film4.uk.title: The Golden Voyage of Sinbad
Film4.uk.description: (1973) Can Sinbad stop a master magician from reaching the Fountain of Destiny on the lost land of Lemuria and being crowned the new leader of Marabia?

Film4.uk.title: Stormbreaker
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Family action-thriller with Alex Pettyfer and Mickey Rourke. British intelligence recruit a schoolboy to take on the man who killed his dad and is planning to unleash a deadly virus.

Film4.uk.title: The Art of Racing in the Rain
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Touching comedy-drama. An ageing golden retriever (voiced by Kevin Costner) tells the story of his life with his best pal, a budding Formula 1 driver.

Film4.uk.title: Turner & Hooch
Film4.uk.description: (1989) Comedy-thriller starring Tom Hanks. A cop investigates a murder to which there's just one witness: Hooch, a slobbering, beer-drinking French mastiff, who now needs 24/7 protection.

Film4.uk.title: See How They Run
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Sam Rockwell and Saoirse Ronan head a splendid ensemble for this comedy whodunnit that places a real murder among a production of Agatha Christie's The Mousetrap. With Adrien Brody.

Film4.uk.title: Assassin Club
Film4.uk.description: (2023) Action with Henry Golding and Sam Neill. An assassin wants to retire for love, but his handler has entered him into a deadly game of hit the hitman. Can he survive to live his dream?

Film4.uk.title: The Spy Who Dumped Me
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Action comedy starring Mila Kunis and Kate McKinnon. Two friends become embroiled in espionage after one of them gets dumped by a man she didn't even know was a spy. Surprise!

Film4.uk.title: Birds of Passage
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Hallucinatory drama charting the rise of the Colombian marijuana trade through its very immediate and profound effect on an indigenous Wayuu tribe. In Wayuu/Spanish/subs.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterday.uk.description: CZ & Nova: The team break with tradition and actually follow Dave Mathewson's advice on what to restore - he points to a 1992 Vauxhall Nova Merit Plus! S2 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Abandoned Engineering
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Escobar's Ruin: A ruined compound on the edge of a peninsula in Colombia which was once home to a famous outlaw and the strange towers looming over red-tinted waters in a Portuguese landscape. S4 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The Great War In Numbers
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Endgame: Hear how the arrival of American forces and an Allied counter-offensive in 1918 helped defeat Germany. Tragically, 11,000 men were killed or injured on Armistice Day. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Southampton to Isle of Wight: Michael Portillo heads from Southampton to the Isle of Wight, where he rides the island's railway, made up of recycled London Underground trains. S2 Ep18

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Lee-on-the-Solent to Bosham: Michael Portillo explores Lee on the Solent in Hampshire, the maritime city of Portsmouth, and Chichester's vast, natural harbour. S2 Ep19

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Wooden Boat: The team restore a 1988 Golf GTI Convertible - an iconic hot hatch - along with a wooden launch boat and catch-up on a Mk1 Austin Mini. S2 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Puch: A super-rare Renault Clio Williams 2 in F1 blue with contrasting gold alloys has turned Dave Mathewson an interesting shade of green. S2 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: True Evil: The Making Of A Nazi

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Bedford Caravanette/MGC: An impressive collection of five iconic cars arrives at Thornton le Dale, including a 1967 Crayford Corsair and a 1966 Ford Zodiac which emerge from a garage in Selby. S4 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Austin 7 Chummy/Triumph TR4A: Derek picks up a lovingly restored 1925 Calthorpe motorbike that he thinks is more of a work of art than anything ever produced by Picasso. S7 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Swift/Toyota Corona/Bedford Van: Derek goes to pick up a veteran 1904 Swift, there's an emotional farewell to a 1980s Bedford HA van, and a Toyota Corona finds a new home. S9 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: MGYB / Yamaha / Quattro: Derek gives the once-over to a Royale Formula Ford race car, and Paul is on a marathon trip to pick up a 1953 MGYB, a Moggy Van, and an '80s Yamaha 250RD motorbike. S9 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Hornsea to Spurn Point: Michael Portillo travels from the seaside resort of Hornsea, to Spurn Point, where he learns about a life-saving 19th-century invention. S2 Ep9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ballarena to Giant's Causeway: Michael Portillo heads to Northern Ireland's Causeway coast beginning a new journey along the north and east coasts through Ulster and Leinster. S2 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Red Star: Following Operation Barbarossa in 1941, the Soviet Army battled the Germans almost alone for two years. Laurence Olivier recounts their efforts as the epic series continues. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Whirlwind: The ultimate guide to World War II, narrated by Laurence Olivier. Bomber Command are unable to hit their targets precisely and attack German cities under cover of darkness. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Tough Old Gut: The hugely respected chronology of WWII. Churchill described Italy as the 'soft underbelly of the crocodile', thinking the Allies could cut through it to reach Germany. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: It's a Lovely Day Tomorrow: Laurence Olivier narrates the acclaimed documentary series on WWII. Hear how Japanese advances across Asia forced the Allies into ignominious retreat. S1 Ep14

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Home Fires: World War II as told by the late Laurence Olivier. Hear more about life on the British Home Front, a time of gas masks, digging for victory and evacuation. S1 Ep15

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Inside the Reich: Laurence Olivier narrates this 26-part series, a milestone in TV history. Germany's progress loses momentum as the tide of the war turns in favour of the Allies. S1 Ep16

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Morning: England became a supply dump as the British and Americans assembled the largest invasion fleet in history for Operation Overlord on 6 June 1944. Laurence Olivier tells all. S1 Ep17

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Occupation: Hear how the Netherlands lived under Nazi rule for four years and how its people decided where their loyalties lay. Narrated by the late, great Laurence Olivier. S1 Ep18

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Pincers: Laurence Olivier provides the narration to this World War II retrospective. Hear how 1944 saw the steady disintegration of the German war machine, as the Allies advanced. S1 Ep19

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Coral Seas: Stunning film sequences and unusual life-forms abound in Sir David Attenborough's natural history of the oceans, which covers the fragile ecosystems of the coral reefs. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Tidal Seas: A history of the deep seas, narrated by Sir David Attenborough. How do the tides affect marine life like stingrays, snails and dolphins? Find out here. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Coasts: David Attenborough explains in his own inimitable way how animals from in and around the sea manage to make use of the constantly changing areas where land meets water. S1 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet II
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: One Ocean: Marine life around the world, from dolphins and tusk fish in a tropical coral reef to walruses struggling to cope with the impact of climate change on the polar north. S2 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet II
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Deep: Creatures that live in volcanic hot spots on the ocean bed, areas that reach temperatures hot enough to melt lead and which may hold the secrets behind all life on Earth. S2 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Volvo P1800/Morris Milk Float: Dave gets wind of a possible free lunch at the officers' mess when he heads off to collect a stylish Swedish Volvo P1800S from an RAF base in the Midlands. S7 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ford Escort Mexico: Derek has sold everything from trucks to bicycles - but he can't remember the last time he auctioned off a two-seater plane. S7 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Dun Laoghaire to Rosslare: Michael Portillo travels from the capital of the Republic of Ireland, Dublin, on the DART suburban railway to the harbour town of Dun Laoghaire. S2 Ep15
